  "texts": [
    "Fine-tuning involves further training of the model using input prompts and the expected outputs.",
    "Utilizing the OpenAI interface with default settings, we fine-tune gpt-3.5-turbo-1106 using 60 samples presenting 5 sentences in each sample with the same prompt as before.",
    "The resulting model improves significantly upon the vanilla (i.e., not finetuned) gpt-3.5-turbo model and exceeds GPT-4 on the F1-macro score.",
    "After fine-tuning, gpt-3.5-turbo becomes much less likely to classify the infrequent dominance categories, while retaining relatively high recall on dominance and coordination, making it the overall best performing model.",
    "While fine-tuning yields significant enhancements, we did not opt for it since it also markedly increases the cost of running inference."
  ],
